"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515218","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-28","<p>At Autumn Statement 2015 it was announced that a transitional period for electricity suppliers to apply the Climate Change Levy exemption on renewably-sourced electricity generated before 1 August 2015 would end on 31 March 2018. This followed an informal consultation by HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) which received 18 written responses. In addition to these responses, HMRC held a number of meetings with organisations affected by the change.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-04-28T16:54:57.553Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515218/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515218/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515218/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-25","Climate Change Levy","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many stakeholders responded to his Department's informal consultation on the transitional arrangements for the removal of the Climate Change Levy exemption for renewably sourced electricity.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","35432"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515219","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-28","<p>At Autumn Statement 2015 it was announced that a transitional period for electricity suppliers to apply the Climate Change Levy exemption on renewably-sourced electricity generated before 1 August 2015 would end on 31 March 2018. This followed an informal consultation by HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC). HMRC informed all respondents of the outcome in letters sent on 26 November 2015. As this was an informal consultation, and some of the responses contain commercially sensitive information, a summary of responses will not be published.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-04-28T14:08:22.093Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515219/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515219/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515219/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-25","Climate Change Levy","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will publish a summary of responses to his Department's informal consultation on the transitional arrangements for the removal of the Climate Change Levy exemption for renewably sourced electricity.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","35437"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515220","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-28","<p>No estimate has been made of the income tax receipts arising from licensed Hackney Carriage drivers. The information is not available and could only be produced at disproportionate cost.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-04-28T14:02:17.747Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515220/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515220/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515220/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-25","Income Tax: Taxis","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the amount of income tax paid annually by London taxi drivers, in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","35450"
