"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515222","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-29","<p>The Treasury continuously monitors global economic developments, including in China, and their impact on the UK as part of the normal process of policy development.</p><p> </p><p>As one of the most open trading economies in the world with a large financial sector, we have to recognise that the UK is not immune to the continued problems being experienced in the world economy.</p><p> </p><p>Nonetheless, the Bank of England’s 2015 stress tests modelled a severe slowdown in commodities and emerging markets. No banks were required to submit revised capital plans following the stress tests. These results indicate that the UK banking system would have the capacity to continue to lend to the real economy, even under such a severe adverse scenario.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-04-29T09:17:39.357Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515222/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515222/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515222/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-25","Debts: China","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he is taking to mitigate the risk posed to the economy by the increased Chinese debt load.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","35463"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515223","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-04","<p>I refer the honourable Member to my previous written answer 34500 of 25 April 2016.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-05-04T12:13:35.697Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515223/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515223/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515223/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-25","London Stock Exchange: Deutsche Borse","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the economic security implications of the proposed merger between the London Stock Exchange and Deutsche Borse.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","35464"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515224","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-29","<p>This is an operational matter for the FCA which is an independent regulator. I have transferred this question across to them and they will respond fully in due course.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","35392","2016-04-29T09:17:24.057Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515224/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515224/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515224/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-25","Financial Services: Misconduct","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many brokers and traders who work in finance have lost their Financial Industry Regulatory Authority licence as a result of financial misconduct since 2008.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","35391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515225","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-29","<p>This is an operational matter for the FCA which is an independent regulator. I have transferred this question across to them and they will respond fully in due course.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","35391","2016-04-29T09:17:23.977Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515225/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515225/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515225/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-25","Financial Services: Misconduct","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many financial firms were fined for financial misconduct in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013, (e) 2014 and (f) 2015; and what the amount of the fine was in each such case.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","35392"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515226","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-04","<p>The information is not held in the form requested.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-05-04T12:28:03.717Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515226/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515226/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515226/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-25","Tax Evasion: Prosecutions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many companies have been prosecuted for tax evasion during the last 10 years; and what revenue has been recovered as a result of those prosecutions.","false","Biography information for Sir Henry Bellingham","North West Norfolk","Sir Henry Bellingham","35377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515227","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-04","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) holds a central record of the number of individuals subject to criminal investigation for tax evasion, together with subsequent prosecutions covering the period from 2011/12 to 2014/15. HMRC does not hold a central record of the number of prosecutions and convictions broken down in this way for earlier years.</p><p> </p><p>The total number of criminal prosecutions of individuals for tax evasion during the period 2011/12 to 2014/15 was 2404. 'Revenue Loss Prevented' is the HMRC management information measure recorded in such cases and the total amount of Revenue Loss Prevented from 2011/12 to 2014/15 was £ 5,070,538,527.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-05-04T12:31:50.38Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515227/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515227/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515227/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-25","Tax Evasion: Prosecutions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people have been prosecuted for tax evasion during the last 10 years; and what revenue has been recovered as a result of those prosecutions.","false","Biography information for Sir Henry Bellingham","North West Norfolk","Sir Henry Bellingham","35378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515228","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-28","<p>HM Treasury’s approach to estimating the net cost of the EU budget to the UK over the long term is set out in Annex B of <em>HM Treasury Analysis: the long-term economic impact of EU membership and the alternatives, </em>publicly available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/517415/treasury_analysis_economic_impact_of_eu_membership_web.pdf</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-04-28T13:57:19.463Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515228/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515228/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515228/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-25","EU Budget","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the UK's (a) payments to the EU, (b) receipts through EU schemes and (c) receipts through the UK rebate in each year between 2020 and 2030.","false","Biography information for Jack Lopresti","Filton and Bradley Stoke","Jack Lopresti","35338"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515229","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-29","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) does allow customers to enter their title but it does not allow customers to enter other honours. Major changes would be required to a wide range of internal HMRC IT services to capture and store this information. The cost of making such changes would be disproportionate.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-04-29T09:17:05.133Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515229/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515229/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515229/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-25","Treasury: Electronic Government","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 21 April 2016 to Question 34465, if HM Revenue and Customs will take steps to enable web-users to include honours when completing government online forms.","false","Biography information for Will Quince","Colchester","Will Quince","35292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515230","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-04","<p>As stated in Spending Review 15 the government supports the ambition to host the 2021 Rugby League World Cup in the Northern Powerhouse.</p><p> </p>Treasury Ministers and officials have meetings with a wide variety of organisations in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery.<p> </p>Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations on departmental business are published on a quarterly basis and are available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","35217 ; 35218 ; 35219 ; 35285","2016-05-04T11:55:28.093Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515230/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515230/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515230/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-25","Rugby: World Cup","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to paragraph 2.256 of Budget 2016, what meetings (a) he and (b) his officials have had with the Department of Health regarding the UK's bid to host the 2021 Rugby League World Cup.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","35286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515231","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-04","<p>The Independent Review of UK Economic Statistics, commissioned by the Chancellor and Minister for the Cabinet Office last summer, suggested that fuller measurement of the economy could add between one-third and two-thirds of a percent to the growth to UK GDP. Better measurement of the digital economy, intangible investment and the sharing economy could therefore improve measurement of output, and thus productivity. The Chancellor welcomed the report’s findings at Budget 2016 and committed to invest over £10m in a new hub for data science, and a centre for excellence for improving measurement of the modern economy.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-05-04T11:43:26.85Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515231/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515231/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515231/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-25","Productivity","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment he has made of the accuracy of the methodology used to measure productivity in the UK.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","35257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515232","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-04","<p>Professor Sir Charles Bean’s Independent Review of Economic Statistics highlighted the importance of proper measurement of the digital economy.</p><p> </p><p>To enable the Office for National Statistics to develop world-leading analytical and digital capabilities in economic measurement, the government will invest over £10m in a new hub for data science and a centre for excellence in economic measurement in line with the recommendations.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-05-04T12:18:13.203Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515232/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515232/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515232/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-25","Digital Technology: Productivity","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to paragraphs 3.16 to 3.26 of the report, Independent review of UK economic statistics, published on 11 March 2016, what plans he has to improve the accuracy of estimates of the contribution of the digital economy to UK productivity.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","35259"
